problems.title: Print ASCII Values
problems.description:
Write a program to print all ASCII characters with their values from start to end.

Input Format:
Two integers start and end separated by space.

Output Format:
Print 'char = value', each on a new line.
problems.examples:
Sample Input
65 67

Sample Output
A = 65
B = 66
C = 67

Explanation:
ASCII values from 65 to 67 are printed.
hintsList: Use a loop from start to end.
Cast the integer to character to print the symbol.
